@startuml

title Service Bootstrap Phases -- IAM / party_cache worked example

participant "main.cpp" as Main
participant "run_signing()" as Runner
participant "registrar::\nregister_handlers()" as Registrar
participant "NATS client\n(own dispatch thread)" as NatsThread
participant "auth_handler" as Auth
participant "party_cache" as Cache
participant "refdata.service" as Refdata

== Phase 1: Wiring & Readiness ==

Main -> Runner : run_signing(io_ctx, nats, ctx, register_fn, on_started)
activate Runner
Runner -> Runner : build RS256 JWT signer
Runner -> Registrar : register_fn(nats, ctx, signer)
activate Registrar

Registrar -> Auth : construct auth_handler(nats, ctx, signer)
Registrar -> NatsThread : subscribe(iam.v1.auth.service-login)
note right of NatsThread
  Live immediately: dispatched on the NATS
  client's own thread (cnats calls the handler
  from a library thread, not io_ctx). Any call
  to this subject can be answered from this
  point on -- even mid-registration.
end note
Registrar -> Registrar : ... subscribe every other IAM subject ...

== Phase 2: Post-Readiness Activities ==

note over Registrar
  Everything this service itself might need to
  CALL (its own subjects included) is already
  live. Safe now to mint tokens, warm caches,
  and do any other work that talks back over NATS.
end note

Registrar -> Cache : construct party_cache(nats)
Registrar -> Registrar : make_service_token_provider(\n  nats, ctx.service_account(), service_password)
Registrar -> NatsThread : request_sync(iam.v1.auth.service-login)
NatsThread -> Auth : dispatch (NATS thread)
Auth --> NatsThread : JWT (service-account token)
NatsThread --> Registrar : JWT
Registrar -> Cache : attach token_provider

Registrar -> Cache : warm_and_subscribe_party_cache(tenant_ids)
loop each known tenant
    Cache -> Refdata : read_parties_for_cache(tenant_id)\nAuthorization: Bearer <JWT>
    Refdata --> Cache : parties
end
Cache -> NatsThread : subscribe(ores.refdata.party_changed)

deactivate Registrar
Runner -> Runner : on_started(io_ctx) -- e.g. spawn heartbeat_publisher
deactivate Runner

== Serving ==

Runner -> Runner : log "Service ready."; wait for shutdown signal
note over Runner
  io_ctx has been running throughout Phases 1-2
  (it hosts this very coroutine). An external
  request to any subscribed subject is served as
  soon as that subject was subscribed in Phase 1 --
  it is not gated on Phase 2 completing.
end note

@enduml
